00:55:14.950 --> 00:55:20.110
AUDIENCE: So I've heard over
the years sort of two competing

00:55:20.110 --> 00:55:21.550
notions of posture.

00:55:21.550 --> 00:55:23.870
And you touched on
one very nicely,

00:55:23.870 --> 00:55:26.860
which is this tensegrity
idea, that the body is

00:55:26.860 --> 00:55:33.550
a dynamic system supported by
elasticity and by structure.

00:55:33.550 --> 00:55:37.300
And then a second one that talks
about this kind of rootedness,

00:55:37.300 --> 00:55:38.620
where you're--

00:55:38.620 --> 00:55:40.190
MARY BOND: Stacks of blocks.

00:55:40.190 --> 00:55:42.010
AUDIENCE: Stacking
your bones and trying

00:55:42.010 --> 00:55:44.470
to make sure that
you're well supported

00:55:44.470 --> 00:55:45.550
through your skeleton.

00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:47.320
Are those actually
contradictory?

00:55:47.320 --> 00:55:52.337
Or is there some underlying
principle behind them both?

00:55:52.337 --> 00:55:53.170
MARY BOND: I don't--

00:55:55.720 --> 00:55:59.980
I like to think
that they both work.

00:55:59.980 --> 00:56:02.680
But if you could have
a stack of blocks

00:56:02.680 --> 00:56:06.220
that was floating in
a tensegral apparatus,

00:56:06.220 --> 00:56:10.180
wouldn't that be better
than just compression, block

00:56:10.180 --> 00:56:12.190
upon block upon block?

00:56:12.190 --> 00:56:15.280
So I think Ida Rolf's
idea was stacks of blocks.

00:56:15.280 --> 00:56:17.380
You saw it in her logo.

00:56:17.380 --> 00:56:21.400
And she also talked a lot
about Buckminster Fuller

00:56:21.400 --> 00:56:22.330
and tensegrity.

00:56:22.330 --> 00:56:26.350
So she had both things
happening when she taught us.

00:56:26.350 --> 00:56:28.750
And I think she just
had it both ways

00:56:28.750 --> 00:56:31.760
and hadn't integrated them.

00:56:31.760 --> 00:56:35.230
And I think that's still true.

00:56:35.230 --> 00:56:38.290
And I know that there are times
when I'm a stack of blocks

00:56:38.290 --> 00:56:41.010
and I can't help it.

00:56:41.010 --> 00:56:45.400
But if you just move more
towards the conception

00:56:45.400 --> 00:56:48.730
that you're a tensegrity,
I think already

00:56:48.730 --> 00:56:56.260
that makes a change in
how you embody this flesh.

00:56:56.260 --> 00:56:58.225
And maybe I'm being too poetic.

